Context: The George Brown College offers financial assistance to students. Interested individuals can learn more about financial assistance options by visiting the college's website. Domestic students may contact the Admissions department at admissions@georgebrown.ca for inquiries, while international students should submit an inquiry through the college's website. The college has committed to sustainability efforts and can be followed on social media for campus news and events. Application deadlines, college news, upcoming events, tours, and other information can be signed up for on the college's website. The contact center can be reached at 416-415-2000 (TTY: 1-877-515-5559) or by emailing ask.george@georgebrown.ca. The college's social media hub can also be visited for more information. All website information is subject to change without notice and should not be considered a representation, offer, or warranty. Students are responsible for verifying George Brown College fee requirements.
